# Runnable — Self-Hosted Directory & Hosting Manager

A web-based application for managing server directories, hosting them via Caddy/Apache/Nginx, integrating with GitHub for auto-deployment, and providing static file hosting — all accessible via `*.runnable.dev` subdomains.

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Client (React + TypeScript + Vite)"
        UI[Web UI :5175]
    end

    subgraph "Server (Node.js + Express + TypeScript)"
        API[REST API :3001]
        WS[WebSocket Server]
        PM[Process Manager]
        GH[GitHub Webhook Handler]
        FM[File Manager]
    end

    subgraph "Data Layer"
        DB[(PostgreSQL)]
        FS[Server Filesystem<br/>SERDIR]
    end

    subgraph "Managed Services"
        CADDY[Caddy]
        NGINX[Nginx]
        APACHE[Apache]
    end

    UI --> API
    UI --> WS
    API --> DB
    API --> FS
    PM --> CADDY
    PM --> NGINX
    PM --> APACHE
    GH --> FS
    FM --> FS
```

**Tech Stack:**

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Frontend | React 18, TypeScript, Vite, React Router, Zustand |
| Backend | Node.js, Express, TypeScript, Socket.IO |
| Database | PostgreSQL + [TypeORM](https://typeorm.io/) |
| Auth | JWT (access + refresh tokens), bcrypt, Passport.js (GitHub/Google OAuth) |
| File Uploads | Multer (configurable max size, default 512MB) |
| Process Mgmt | `child_process` + systemd integration |

