### 7. Sandboxed Environment

All system-level operations (git commands, server processes, file operations) run inside a sandboxed execution layer:

#### [NEW] [server/src/services/sandbox.service.ts](file:///Users/araasryan/AndroidStudioProjects/runnable/server/src/services/sandbox.service.ts)

**Approach**: Each project runs in an isolated environment using:

1. **Dedicated Unix user per project** — `useradd runnable-<projectId>` with restricted permissions
2. **chroot or namespace isolation** — project processes can only access their own directory
3. **Resource limits** — via `ulimit` / cgroups: max CPU, memory, open files, disk quota
4. **Network restrictions** — projects bind only to their assigned internal port
5. **Command allowlist** — only permitted commands (`git`, `caddy`, `nginx`, `apache2`) can be executed

```typescript
class SandboxService {
  // Execute command in sandboxed context
  async exec(projectId: string, command: string, args: string[]): Promise<ExecResult>
  // Create sandbox for new project (user, directory, limits)
  async createSandbox(projectId: string, directoryPath: string): Promise<void>
  // Tear down sandbox on project deletion
  async destroySandbox(projectId: string): Promise<void>
}
```

The sandbox wraps all calls in [process.service.ts](file:///Users/araasryan/AndroidStudioProjects/runnable/server/src/services/process.service.ts), [github.service.ts](file:///Users/araasryan/AndroidStudioProjects/runnable/server/src/services/github.service.ts), and [fileManager.service.ts](file:///Users/araasryan/AndroidStudioProjects/runnable/server/src/services/fileManager.service.ts).

