## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Caddy as the primary reverse proxy**: Even if a user chooses Apache/Nginx for their project, the master reverse proxy (handling `*.runnable.dev` routing + custom domains) will always be Caddy. The user's chosen server type runs on an internal port behind it.

> [!NOTE]
> **Sandboxed execution**: All system-level operations run through the [SandboxService](file:///Users/araasryan/AndroidStudioProjects/runnable/server/src/services/sandbox.service.ts#17-103) with per-project Unix users, resource limits, and restricted filesystem access (see §7).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **OAuth setup required**: GitHub and Google OAuth will need registered OAuth applications. The client IDs and secrets must be configured in [.env](file:///Users/araasryan/AndroidStudioProjects/runnable/.env) before those auth methods work. Local username/password auth will work out of the box.

